Busia county election manager Fredrick Apopa has said any perpetrator of violence during the election will be punished.He said he will ensure a free, fair and transparent election in August.Apopa spoke during a meeting with party nominees in Matayos constituency IEBC office on Tuesday.&ldquo;We have clear laws and the Election Act that explains how candidates should conduct themselves,&rdquo; he said.The meeting was attended by Busia Deputy Governor Kizito Wangalwa.Wangalwa defended NASA presidential flagbearer Raila Odinga&rsquo;s call to support only alliance candidates and reject independents.&ldquo;You know when a father says something a child is not supposed to argue, but follow what he says. The party leader has given direction,&rdquo; he said.Woman rep hopeful Susan Mangeni said female candidates need protection.